08/09/2008
ATHENS, Greece -- A passenger train collided with a truck at an intersection near the central Greek town of Larissa, killing two people and injuring another late on Saturday (September 6th), media reported on Sunday. The truck's driver and the train's conductor died in the accident. One female passenger was slightly injured. Greece's railway service cancelled all local train routes between Larissa, Thessaloniki and Volos for the rest of the day. (ERT, In.news, Naftemporiki, Kathimerini, SKAI, AP - 07/09/08)
